Privacy Policy for AI-Discord-Bot

Effective Date: September 6, 2025

AI-Discord-Bot (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you interact with our Discord bot.

1. Information We Collect

Discord Data: We may access your username, Discord ID, messages, and server interactions solely to provide bot functionality.

Direct Messages: Any DMs you send to the bot may be logged or forwarded to the bot administrator for support or moderation purposes.

AI Queries: When you use AI commands (e.g., /ask), your queries are sent to OpenAI’s servers for processing. We do not store AI responses long-term.

2. How We Use Your Information

To provide and improve bot functionality.

To moderate content and ensure community safety.

To debug, audit, or troubleshoot bot performance issues.

3. Data Sharing

We do not sell or rent your personal information.

Your data may be shared with OpenAI in order to process AI queries.

Information may be disclosed if required by law or to prevent abuse.

4. Data Security

We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data.

However, no system is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Third-Party Services

Our bot uses OpenAI services, which may have their own privacy policies.

We recommend reviewing OpenAI’s Privacy Policy at https://openai.com/privacy
.

6. Your Rights

You may request deletion of your data or inquire about our processing practices by contacting the bot administrator.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The latest version will always be posted publicly.

Contact Us

For questions regarding this Privacy Policy, contact the bot administrator via Discord DM.
